# Modularity Core ‚Äî Cursor / AI Editor Rules

This is the `modularity/core` Laravel package. Read AGENTS.md for the complete guide.

## Quick facts

- PHP ^8.2, Laravel >=11.0
- Namespace: `Modularity\`
- Source: `src/`  Config: `config/modularity.php`  Migrations: `database/migrations/`
- Stubs: `stubs/module/`  Tests: `tests/`

## Must-know rules (enforce these in all code suggestions)

1. **Every ModuleServiceProvider must declare `protected string $slug`** matching the slug
   in `module.json`. Missing it causes a runtime error.

2. **Module tables MUST include a `tenant_id` column** (`unsignedBigInteger`, indexed).
   Models must use `BelongsToTenant` trait or extend `ModuleModel`.

3. **Slug format is strictly kebab-case**: `/^[a-z0-9]+(?:-[a-z0-9]+)*$/`
   Valid: `my-module` Invalid: `MyModule`, `my_module`, `My Module`

4. **Boot is gated**: `ModuleServiceProvider::boot()` returns early if the module is not
   active for the current tenant. Routes, views, listeners ‚Äî nothing loads unless active.

5. **Install before activate**: A module must be installed globally before it can be
   activated for a tenant. Dependencies must be installed before dependents.

6. **Migrations are never rolled back**: Even `module:remove` preserves data.
   Never suggest `php artisan migrate:rollback` for module migrations.

7. **Use `Module::config()` only when a tenant is set**: It returns the default silently
   when `Tenant::id()` is null.

8. **Setting the tenant is the host app's job**: prefer `Tenant::set($user->tenant_id)` in
   your own auth flow. The built-in resolver chain defaults to `session` only; `subdomain`,
   `domain`, and `header` are opt-in, require `MODULARITY_TENANT_MODEL`, and read
   attacker-controllable input ‚Äî a resolved tenant ID is identity, not authorization.

## Primary facades

```php
use Modularity\Support\Facades\Module;
use Modularity\Support\Facades\Tenant;

Module::active('slug')              // bool ‚Äî current tenant
Module::activeFor('slug', $id)      // bool ‚Äî specific tenant
Module::installed('slug')           // bool
Module::menu()->add([...])          // register navigation
Module::config('slug', 'key', null) // per-tenant settings
Tenant::set(1); Tenant::id(); Tenant::assertSet(); Tenant::forget();
```

## Artisan commands

```bash
php artisan module:make-module <Name> [--livewire]
php artisan module:install <slug>
php artisan module:activate <slug> --tenant=<id>
php artisan module:deactivate <slug> --tenant=<id> | --all-tenants
php artisan module:upgrade <slug>
php artisan module:remove <slug> [--force]
php artisan module:list [--tenant=<id>]
php artisan module:status <slug>
```

## Module structure

```
Modules/<Name>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ module.json                       ‚Üê required: name, slug, version, providers
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ src/Providers/<Name>ServiceProvider.php  ‚Üê extends ModuleServiceProvider
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ database/migrations/              ‚Üê run at module:install
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ routes/web.php  routes/api.php    ‚Üê auto-loaded when active
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ resources/views/                  ‚Üê namespace: <slug>::view-name
```

